{
  "texts": [
    "Experimental setupIn the developed research work, a novel mechanism was implemented to predict human motion intention in the Python Platform.",
    "To execute the effective DR classification, population counts were considered as 10, chromosome length was taken as 4, and maximum iteration counts were used as 50.",
    "Different optimization techniques used in the developed framework were Black Widow Optimization (BWO) 45, Monarch Butterfly Optimization (MBO) 46, Arithmetic Optimization Algorithm (AOA) 47 and YGSA 43.",
    "Conventional DR classifiers used in the validation were ELM 30, CNN 33, LSTM 41, AH-CNN-LSTM, Deep Neural Network (DNN) 48, Res-LSTM 42 and AH-CNN-Res-LSTM.",
    "Validation metricsDifferent computation metrics utilized in the developed framework are detailed as follows."
  ]
}